13 through an alternative route to licensure. (NRS 391.019) Section 1 of this bill
14 requires such regulations to authorize a person to simultaneously enroll in multiple
15 programs for an alternative route to licensure.
16 Existing law requires a public elementary school to: (1) establish a plan to
17 monitor the growth of certain pupils who have a deficiency in the subject area of
18 reading; and (2) regularly assess the growth of a pupil for whom a plan is
19 established. (NRS 392.755) Section 3 of this bill requires a plan to monitor the
20 growth of such a pupil to use, to the greatest extent possible, assessments
21 administered on a school-wide or grade level-wide basis for the purpose of
22 regularly assessing the growth of a pupil.
