5 Sec. 2. NRS 391.100 is hereby amended to read as follows:
6 391.100 1. The board of trustees of a school district [may] :
7 (a) May employ a superintendent of schools, teachers and all
8 other necessary employees.
9 (b) Shall not require a prospective school administrator to
10 complete a preservice program for aspiring administrators as a
11 condition precedent to applying for employment as a school
12 administrator.
13 2. The board of trustees of a school district:
14 (a) May employ teacher aides and paraprofessionals to assist
15 licensed personnel in the instruction or supervision of children,
16 either in the classroom or at any other place in the school or on the
17 grounds thereof. A person who is employed as a paraprofessional by
18 a school district to work in a program supported with Title I money
19 must possess the requirements prescribed by the State Board
20 pursuant to NRS 391.094.
21 (b) Shall establish policies governing the duties and
22 performance of teacher aides.
23 3. As used in this section “preservice program for aspiring
24 administrators” means a structured training program designed to
25 prepare a prospective administrator to become a school leader by
26 equipping the prospective administrator with the necessary skills
27 and knowledge to manage a school effectively. The term includes,
28 without limitation, an aspiring administrator or assistant principal
29 development program. The term does not include a course of study
30 in administration required to receive a license or endorsement as a
31 professional administrator of a school.
32 Sec. 3. NRS 392.755 is hereby amended to read as follows:
33 392.755 1. A public elementary school that has notified the
34 parent or legal guardian of a pupil that, based upon the results of
35 state or local assessments, it has been determined that the pupil has a
36 deficiency in the subject area of reading pursuant to NRS 392.750
37 shall, within 30 days after providing such notice, establish a plan to
38 monitor the growth of the pupil in the subject area of reading.
39 2. A plan to monitor the growth of a pupil in the subject area of
40 reading must be established by a licensed teacher and any other
41 relevant licensed school personnel and approved by the principal of
42 the school and the parent or legal guardian of the pupil. The plan
43 must include a description of any intervention services and intensive
44 instruction that will be provided to the pupil to correct the area of
45 deficiency and must include that the pupil will receive intensive
